00:09:10.640 --> 00:09:14.880
There are a couple of different areas that you can think about with this and how it relates.

00:09:14.880 --> 00:09:20.919
Like if you were to work in an insurance company, zero to one happened decades ago.

00:09:20.919 --> 00:09:25.919
You know, the data tends to be incredibly tightly controlled, very, very, well, relativistically

00:09:25.919 --> 00:09:28.799
clean, relatively clean, right?

00:09:28.799 --> 00:09:32.520
There are actuaries, there are patterns, there are processes for how you can optimize and

00:09:32.520 --> 00:09:36.919
kind of what the walls and constraints are for your models with respect to what features

00:09:36.919 --> 00:09:41.440
you can use, you know, governance, that sort of thing.

00:09:41.440 --> 00:09:48.080
Some companies, this is not the only one that benefits like this, where data science is

00:09:48.080 --> 00:09:50.719
a newly discovered talent, more or less.

00:09:50.719 --> 00:09:54.479
And this has been going on at Kraft for quite some time, about five years.

00:09:54.479 --> 00:10:02.440
So not to claim that it's brand new, but you have to integrate more complicated processes

00:10:02.440 --> 00:10:06.020
into systems that were never originally designed for, right?

00:10:06.119 --> 00:10:15.059
So if you're looking at Goliath monostack platforms and you're trying to say, hey, we

00:10:15.059 --> 00:10:20.539
need to inject all these models into this old Java system, you can get a lot of pushback

00:10:20.539 --> 00:10:21.539
on that.

00:10:21.539 --> 00:10:26.700
So it's learning how to be dynamic and how to create and how to create, I guess, value

00:10:26.700 --> 00:10:34.460
capture and build new systems in a way that's also hospitable and can be ingested into something

00:10:34.460 --> 00:10:36.820
that was never originally designed for it.

00:10:36.820 --> 00:10:42.219
This also relates to business processes where you can be working with, you know, salespeople,

00:10:42.219 --> 00:10:50.099
marketing, other business folks where they have always had universal control over a process

00:10:50.099 --> 00:10:59.900
and then to inject math, which may be seen as witchcraft to some, into their decision

00:10:59.900 --> 00:11:04.659
processes in a way that might be a little adversarial or controversial for what they

00:11:04.659 --> 00:11:08.380
might originally think, but, you know, helping them along to kind of get them into a more

00:11:08.380 --> 00:11:09.859
optimal flow state.

00:11:09.859 --> 00:11:12.820
So it is very, very tricky.

00:11:12.820 --> 00:11:18.219
And it comes down largely to one interpretability, as we talked about with our models and understanding

00:11:18.219 --> 00:11:22.599
